article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 106, Alma 57
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Larry Wright scored a career-high 22 points and Oakland, Mich., cruised to a 106-57 victory over Division III Alma on Monday night. Wright was 6 of 7 from long range to equal his career high for 3-pointers. Keith Benson added 15 points and 11 rebounds for the Golden Grizzlies (7-7). Cory Schneider had 15 points to lead the Scots (3-7). Ilija Milutinovic and Ledrick Eackles each had career highs in points with 12 and 11, respectively, for Oakland, which led 59-22 at halftime. Jonathon Jones broke the school record with his 114th game started for the Golden Grizzlies. Oakland scored the first 15 points of the game and led by as many as 55.
